comments: White (BOS) releases the ball prior to his foot coming down out of bounds.
Tatum (BOS) lowers his right arm down towards the ball and avoids making any illegal contact with Green (DAL) during his contest of the layup attempt.
Tatum's (BOS) off-arm comes out slightly as he releases away from Washington (DAL) at the end of the drive and the contact is marginal.
Lively II (DAL) firms up over his right leg in Holiday's (BOS) path and marginal lower body contact occurs as Holiday defends over the pick.
White (BOS) establishes himself in Green's (DAL) path and does not deliver any illegal contact when setting the pick.
Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) hand lightly brushes Brown's (BOS) front during his drive and the contact is marginal.
Irving (DAL) grasps and immediately releases White's (BOS) jersey during his drive toward the paint and the contact is marginal.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Green (DAL) delivers contact to Horford (BOS), which dislodges him. The ball does not come down out of bounds prior to Horford regathering it and releasing it before falling out of bounds. This should have been assessed as a foul on Green. Coach Mazzulla (BOS) attempts to call a timeout, however, given that Boston does not have possession, a timeout request is not granted.
Horford (BOS) legally contests Irving's (DAL) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Washington (DAL) clamps and pulls White's (BOS) right arm, which impacts his ability to secure the rebound.
Green (DAL) releases the throw-in within five seconds.
Tatum (BOS) and Irving (DAL) come together during the inbound and the contact is marginal.
White (BOS) grabs Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) left arm in an effort to commit a take foul.
Green (DAL) commits a take foul on Tatum (BOS). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Horford (BOS) commits a take foul on Washington (DAL).. The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
